sentences: Noah Adrian Gordon (born September 19, 1971, in Sparta, Illinois) is an American country music singer and songwriter.
There, he released his debut album I Need a Break on February 7, 1995.
The album produced the single "The Blue Pages," which spent three weeks on the Billboard country charts, peaking at No. 68.
In January 1999, Gordon and Bryan Austin, also a former Patriot Records recording artist, founded a band called Phoenix.
